Package com.jgalgo.io

Interface GraphReader

  • public interface GraphReader
    A reader that reads Graphs from files/IO-reader. 
     
 Graph g = GraphReader.newInstance("gml").readGraph("graph1.gml");
 System.out.println("g's vertices are: " + g.vertices());
    Author:
    Barak Ugav

      • newInstance

        static GraphReader newInstance​(String format)
        Get new GraphReader instance by a format name.

        Any one of the following formats is supported: ['csv', 'dimacs', 'gexf', 'gml', 'graph6', 'space6', 'graphml', 'leda']

        Parameters:
        format - the name of the format
        Returns:
        a reader that can read graphs of the given format
